# Search-exclusion artifact (Shipshape fitting-out derived).
#
# Reach: ripgrep and ag TRAVERSAL only. This file alone is not a bulkhead.
# Proven safe forms:   `rg <pattern>`, `rg -t md <pattern>`, `rg --hidden`.
# Proven bypasses:     `rg --glob '*.md'`, `rg --no-ignore`, `rg -u`;
#                      any shell glob expanded into an explicit path list,
#                      such as `rg *.md`, since an explicitly named path is
#                      searched whatever this file says; and GNU grep, which
#                      never reads this file at all, so a bare `grep -r`
#                      reaches the notes with no flags.
#
# The construction-level exclusion is the Shipshape Bash custody hook, which
# must deny those vectors for internal roles. Captain still opens the notes
# by path.
CAPTAIN.md
